Class AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.sgdpllt.core.solver.AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExpressionLiteralSplitterStepSolver, ExpressionStepSolver, LiteralSplitterStepSolver<Expression>, StepSolver<Expression>, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBooleanWithPropagatedLiteralsRequiringPropagatedLiteralsAndCNFToBeSatisfiedStepSolver, AbstractModelCountingWithPropagatedLiteralsImportedFromSatisfiabilityStepSolver, AbstractSingleVariableNumericConstraintFeasibilityRegionStepSolver

    @Beta
public abstract class AbstractExpressionWithPropagatedLiteralsStepSolver
extends Object
implements ExpressionLiteralSplitterStepSolver
    An abstract implementation for step solvers for problems based on a propagated literals, and a propagated CNF.

    Propagated literals are literals required to be true (if they are not, the solver step returns is provided by the abstract method getSolutionExpressionGivenContradiction()). In fact, this class allows a generalization of propagated literals in the form of a propagated CNF.

    Extensions defined which are the propagated literals and propagated CNF through the abstract methods getPropagatedLiterals(Context) and getPropagatedCNFBesidesPropagatedLiterals(Context), which are aggregated by method getPropagatedLiterals(Context).

    Such problems will typically involve a Constraint, so this class provides methods for storing that as well.

    Author:
    braz
